    interpretation: `《罗摩衍那》作为印度两大史诗之一，其对凯拉萨的描述具有深远的宗教和文化影响。这段引文不仅描绘了凯拉萨的自然壮丽，更重要的是确立了它作为湿婆神圣居所的地位。

值得注意的是，史诗中的凯拉萨仍然带有浓厚的神话色彩，地理描述较为模糊。这反映了早期印度教对喜马拉雅山脉的神圣化过程——将自然地理转化为宗教象征。罗摩派遣哈奴曼前往凯拉萨的情节，也体现了印度教中「神使朝圣」的传统，即通过神圣使者完成凡人与神灵之间的沟通。

对于现代印度教徒而言，这段史诗仍然是朝圣冈仁波齐的精神动力之一。每年参加Kailash Mansarovar Yatra的印度教徒，在出发前往往会诵读这段经文，以坚定自己的朝圣决心。`,
    interpretationEn: `As one of India's two great epics, the Ramayana's description of Kailasa has profound religious and cultural influence. This passage not only depicts Kailasa's natural grandeur but more importantly establishes its status as Shiva's sacred abode.

Notably, the epic's Kailasa still carries strong mythological coloring with vague geographical descriptions. This reflects early Hinduism's sacralization of the Himalayas—transforming natural geography into religious symbolism. The episode of Rama dispatching Hanuman to Kailasa also embodies the Hindu tradition of "divine messenger pilgrimage," where sacred emissaries facilitate communication between mortals and deities.

For modern Hindus, this epic remains one of the spiritual motivations for pilgrimage to Mount Kailash. Indian pilgrims participating in the annual Kailash Mansarovar Yatra often recite this scripture before departure to strengthen their resolve.`
