这本书为理解冈仁波齐和玛旁雍错的宗教关系提供了独特的视角。`,
    fullQuoteEn: `"Sacred Mountain and Holy Lake: Kailash and Manasarovar" is an academic work specifically studying Kailash and Lake Manasarovar. It provides in-depth analysis of the relationship between these two sacred sites:

"Lake Manasarovar's waters are clear as a mirror, reflecting Kailash's majestic form. In Tibetan legend, these waters are the nectar of the Western Heaven's Jade Pool, capable of washing away earthly sins and troubles. Hindus believe that bathing in Manasarovar can purify accumulated karma and gain Shiva's blessings."

Regarding Manasarovar's religious significance, the book records:

"In Tibetan Buddhism, Manasarovar is the residence of Chakrasamvara's consort—Vajravarahi. The water's clarity symbolizes wisdom's purity; the lake's calmness symbolizes the mind's tranquility. Every pilgrim meditates by the lake, seeking inner peace."

The book also describes the correspondence between Manasarovar and Kailash:

